Description: Part of a jar of pale brown pottery: with a red slip on the exterior. The outer surface bears an incised mark, consisting of a single sign of square form. Good condition.
Curator's comments: Compare W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pls.LV-LVI; W. M. F. Petrie 'Tarkhan I and Memphis V', pls.XXX, 30; XXXI, nos. 126, 141, 143-5; W. B. Emery, ‘Excavations at Saqqara : the tomb of Hemaka' (Cairo, 1938), pl.40, nos. 190D, 190F; W. B. Emery, 'Great tombs of the First Dynasty; excavations at Sakkara' II' (London, 1954), 78, fig. 100, nos. 46-8.
